IFFR/VIR/LIVC-SMPL/2017/May/7 -    
1. Leak noted from #2 generator LO cooler sea water inlet valve.,   
2. Main engine Turbocharger exhaust thermometer defective,   
3. Steam leak noted from LO purifier heater drain line.,   
4. Level marking for minimum water level required for hyper mist operation is not highlighted on tank near  gauge glass.,   
5. Few fire extinguishers in engine room- EGB deck, last check date is overdue.,   
6. Steam leak found on relief valve after reducing valve- 10k line.,   
7. Incinerator furnace shows deteriorated condition at few locations.,   
8. Improper emergency exit signs in steering gear room. Painted yellow at higher location which wouldn't assist during emergency- shown to 2E.,   
9. No 3 F.O.T (S) bunker tank steam heating coil valve not holding and the tank temperature is around 60 deg C.,   
10. ER blower flaps closing valve found tight and restricted movement i.e. needs extra effort in closing.,   
11. ME #3 UNIT J.C.W temp local gauge not working,   
12. Welding area apron in workshop found in torn condition,   
13. Old defective loose lifting gear (wire slings) found in engine store room.,   
14. Many pumps, especially bottom deck and ballast pump,  do not have safety guards.,   
15. No record showing incinerator alarm testing between 19-Dec-2017 and 06-Apr/2017.,   
16. Rust stains noted on gland packing casing of emergency fire pump.,   
17. Steam leak noticed on main steam pipe line above boiler FD fan are- 3 no.,   
18. EGB boiler circulating water pump inlet Differential pressure found mal-functioning.,   
19. Fire line drain valve on deck (aft of pump room) found leaking.,   
20. DO filling/transfer valve (to transfer pump) found in seized condition on deck (aft of pump room).,   
21. Oil/water mixture found inside Lifeboat (port) engine casing/ cover.,   
22. Hatchet kept inside stbd lifeboat shows rust stains at the cutting edge.,   
23. Fire doors inside accommodation on B and C decks were found not closing fully. Fire door of fire station also found not closing fully.,   
24. Eye wash bottle was missing in SOPEP locker.,   
25. Water mixing faucet in "owners cabin" and inside hospital found leaking.,   
26. Chain block hook found directly hooked on to alternator bearing casing lifting eye.,   
27. Oil found on top of remote hydraulic valve operating pumps LO tank.,   
28. Crew change room found in poor condition.,   
29. Excess grease found on save all under forward hydraulic pumps,   
30. Gymnasiaum equipment and weights arrangements noted to be in poor condition.,   
31. Thick rust spots noted between frames 79-83,   
32. Vapor manifold end cover bolts noted of shorter length.,   
33. Windlass greasing found in-adequate,   
34. External condition of eye wash container in mid-ship store seen in poor rusted condition.,   
35. Walkway checker plates shows rust spots all the way extending from mid-ship crane until accommodation  area.,   
36. Marking/ stenciling showing number of persons etc at port gangway area not clear.,   
37. Port side gangway wires showed dry condition.,   
38. Engine casing shows weeping rust marks and rust spots at various location.,   
39. Drain on engine funnel deck found not draining well.,   
40. Auxiliary boiler fuel oil heater relief valve found leaking.,   
41. HFO purifiers de-sludge drain hoses showed traces of leak on them.,   
42. Anti-splash tapes found torn/ missing on FO circulating pump flanges and other locations,   
43. Main engine fuel linkage showed in-sufficient greasing.

IFFR/VIR/LIVC-SMPL/2017/Aug/22 -    
1. Funnel stack painting - pipes have a lot of soot stain and stacks have large rust patches with no paint coatings,   
2. ISPS sand bunkers inadequate,   
3. Denso tape on the bottom of the main mast stay appears dry; for the other stays, the tapes were only at the bottom and freshly replaced,   
4. Excessive soot generation observed - Funnel deck and poop deck have excessive soot accumulation,   
5. Filter placed in the intake mesh for the aft E/R blowers clogged with soot - this may be a fire hazard (done by staff to prevent the intake of soot and to prevent the entry of oil vapour from the  oily mist catcher),   
6. Loose grating on the funnel deck - this was being used to prevent particles from clogging the scupper drain filter,   
7. No Eyewash in the paint room,   
8. Several lifebuoys had lifelines and SI light lanyard were tethered on the Grab lines instead of the body,   
9. Lifebuoy Approval label was faded on the port aft Lifebuoy,   
10. Bridge wing Lifebuoy SI light tethering lanyard not as per requirement (should be at least 3.6 as per manual),   
11. SWL for lifting eye - pads for the E/R opening on upperdeck not marked - similarly not marked in P/R and in some places in E/R,   
12. Some stenciling of air purge units will help easily identify the tanks being serviced more easily,   
13. Finishing of work is not upto mark - several areas where nipples are painted over, bolts are painted over without any evidence of application of grease,   
14. ECDIS - Anchor swinging circle - OOW aware of manually calculating but indicated that they allow ECDIS to calculate automatically,   
15. A/Co remarkd not entered in logbook however noted in GPS log; Emphasis seems to be on entering generic commenst such as "Compasses compared, Courses Checked" instead of making relevant significant event entries,   
16. Safety depth entry was incorrect; error in calculation,   
17. Excessive Oil noted in saveall under #1 Steering gear Hydraulic morot oil seal,   
18. Engineer officer to be familiar with entering the record for the testing of alarms for steering gear as part of the pre-arrival and pre-departure routine (this is otherwise to be weekly routine if too many frequent ports),   
19. 110V Low Insulation reading around 4 Mohm; alarm setting is at 5 Mohm but presently keeping lower setting,   
20. Soft patch on discharge side of Fire and GS pump - to enter into SHIPPALM,   
21. Fwd stbd side bilge to be cleaned of Debris / rust stains - slighlty darkened water,   
22. Workshop - Grinder spark arrest flap to be cleaned of debris and gap adjusted to correct clearance of 3-10 mm,   
23. ER Store - aft area to be cleared up of unneccessary items and squared up better - most of the workshop was well stacked,   
24. There was no record of air cleaning filter unit of being replaced after 40 running hours - entry not made; ditto fro changing of compressor oil,   
25. Entries in the FFA log were generic in nature and not accurate - for eg all SCBA bottles had 150 bar pressure (including the spare bottles) though only 4 bottles were routinely charged every week,   
26. Monthlyand quarterly FFA entries not streamlined in log - no entries for Low Expansion foam, list of vents, fire hydrants, Foam and Fire isolation valves and for fire hoses pressure testing,   
27. 2 nos DCP fire ext for Lifeboats do not have any spares,   
28. Oil streaks IWO B/Hd seal for vac pump #1 and #3 (more for #1),   
29. Leak on open side hydraulic inlet connector of V/V WB 328 valve actuator,   
30. #2 WBP and #1 COP casing previously opened and boxed back but nuts not greased and no touch up paint applied over the opened areas,   
31. Thick rust noted under #1 WBP strainer and on adjacent weld seam,   
32. Bilge needs brightening up - too much loose dirt debris lying around - needs sweepeing and mopping
